Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All measured values are within or close to normal ranges, except for mildly elevated chloride and total cholesterol. HbA1c is at the upper limit of normal, suggesting good but borderline glycemic control. Lipid profile shows slightly elevated total cholesterol with acceptable LDL and HDL levels. Renal function, electrolytes, and glucose are unremarkable. No acute laboratory concerns; recommend monitoring cholesterol and glycemic control.
